{
  "text": "It has been shown that there is a relationship between structural connectivity (SC), the physical white-matter tracts between regions, and resting state functional connectivity (FC), the temporal coactivations between regions [CITATION_1] Hermundstad et al., 2013; [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] van den Heuvel, Mandl, Kahn, & Hulshoff Pol, 2009; van den Heuvel & Sporns, 2013) using both simple linear [CITATION_8] ) as well as more complex metrics [CITATION_9] .",
